The most important thing was because over there the lifestyle was different.

00:10:18.000 --> 00:10:22.000
Even though you didn't have much but you were happy.

00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:28.000
Sometimes the family used to take you on picnics and things which we were looking forward to there.

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:30.000
And it was nice.

00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:34.000
Food wise you had your own.

00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:38.000
The food we ate there was nice, fresh.

00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:40.000
And it was different from here.

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:44.000
When we came first we missed all that.

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:48.000
Because it was totally different.

00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:52.000
It was good times as well and bad times.

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:56.000
So what about the culture as well?

00:10:56.000 --> 00:11:00.000
What was the culture and your practice of the culture?

00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:02.000
Here?

00:11:02.000 --> 00:11:04.000
In the beginning it was hard.

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:08.000
But the thing is when we were living, staying there because we knew there were no Asians.

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:12.000
So we had to adapt to wear English clothes as well.

00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:16.000
When you go to work you can wear your own clothes.

00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:20.000
Because you'll be an old one out.

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:22.000
You had to start adapting to it.

00:11:22.000 --> 00:11:24.000
But we still kept our culture.

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:28.000
Till now I try to keep my culture.

00:11:28.000 --> 00:11:32.000
But the children, they do half.

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:36.000
How were you able to keep your culture?

00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:38.000
What things were you doing?

00:11:38.000 --> 00:11:46.000
When there's an occasion, or when there's respect for the elders.

00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:48.000
Or if there's a death they must go and respect.

00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:50.000
This is all our culture.

00:11:50.000 --> 00:11:56.000
You can sit with them and make some time and sympathize with them.

00:11:56.000 --> 00:11:58.000
They're emotional.

00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:02.000
Don't forget your culture.

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:04.000
Keep your culture going with your food specially.

00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:06.000
Your language.

00:12:06.000 --> 00:12:08.000
It's number one.

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:10.000
It happened with my children.

00:12:10.000 --> 00:12:14.000
My mother-in-law showed that my children had to have the mother tongue.

00:12:14.000 --> 00:12:16.000
No English was allowed.

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:20.000
Where now my grandchildren don't even speak our language.

00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:22.000
Because they speak English.

00:12:22.000 --> 00:12:24.000
The parents are English speaking to the kids.

00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:26.000
Which we don't like it.

00:12:26.000 --> 00:12:28.000
We're not happy.

00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:30.000
But these days you can't say nothing to them.

00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:32.000
You try to guide them the right way.

00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:34.000
When you come to your religion, you guide them to keep your religion.

00:12:34.000 --> 00:12:36.000
Don't go off to track.

00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:40.000
Don't change into yourself too westernized.

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:42.000
Because I'm open minded.

00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:44.000
So we leave it to half and half.

00:12:44.000 --> 00:12:46.000
And don't push them too much.

00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:52.000
But I still want them to carry on with little bit which we got in our culture.

00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:54.000
You know.

00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:56.000
Like we have our festivals and things.

00:12:56.000 --> 00:12:58.000
They should know about it.

00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:00.000
And on that day we must get together.

00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:02.000
And share food and all that.

00:13:02.000 --> 00:13:06.000
If you didn't remind them, they'll know about it.

00:13:06.000 --> 00:13:10.000
Because there's so many other distractions now that can really deter away the people.

00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:12.000
And most of the time they're in school.

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:14.000
They live in school more than.

00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:16.000
And work.

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:20.000
They're only in the evening for a little short time.

00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:22.000
We still live in Ponty Prid.

00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:24.000
No, I live in Newport.

